I would not call this design "Aethelon" if it's going into your portfolio.

The design itself deserves to be treated as a standalone flagship concept.

# Project Name

**Obsidian Atelier**

**Tagline:**
*Where Matter Becomes Meaning.*

Alternative names:

* Velour Studio
* Nocturne House
* Atelier No. VII
* Monument Living
* Forme Atelier
* Aurelius Interiors
* Studio Solenne

My favorite is still:

# Obsidian Atelier

It sounds expensive, memorable, and design-award friendly.

---

# MASTER AGENT PROMPT

Use this as the full prompt for Cursor, Claude Code, OpenAI Codex, Lovable, Bolt, or any AI web-development agent.

---

# SYSTEM / PROJECT PROMPT

You are an award-winning creative director, senior product designer, interaction designer, art director, and frontend engineer.

Your goal is to design and build a world-class luxury furniture and interior design landing page called:

# OBSIDIAN ATELIER

Tagline:

"Where Matter Becomes Meaning."

The final result must feel worthy of:

* Awwwards Site of the Day
* FWA
* CSS Design Awards
* Behance Interaction Design Feature

This is NOT an ecommerce website.

This is NOT a template website.

This is NOT SaaS.

This is a luxury digital experience.

Every section should feel intentional, editorial, cinematic, and premium.

The website should blend:

* Apple-level polish
* Luxury fashion editorial layouts
* Modern architecture magazines
* High-end interior design studios
* Museum exhibition experiences

Avoid anything that feels:

* Generic
* Bootstrap-like
* Template-based
* Corporate
* Startup-like
* Dashboard-like

The website should communicate exclusivity, craftsmanship, heritage, and timeless design.

---

# VISUAL DIRECTION

Color palette:

Background:
#F7F4EF

Primary Text:
#171717

Accent:
#A67C52

Dark Sections:
#0B0B0B

Secondary Text:
#6A6A6A

Borders:
rgba(0,0,0,.08)

---

# TYPOGRAPHY

Headlines:

Cormorant Garamond

or

Canela

or

Bodoni Moda

Body:

Inter

or

Neue Haas Grotesk

or

General Sans

Typography should carry most of the luxury feeling.

Use large elegant headlines.

Generous spacing.

Large margins.

Editorial compositions.

---

# GLOBAL DESIGN RULES

Use:

* large whitespace
* asymmetrical layouts
* layered compositions
* subtle motion
* premium micro interactions
* elegant hover states

Avoid:

* gradients everywhere
* glassmorphism
* neumorphism
* excessive shadows
* excessive animations

Everything should feel restrained.

Luxury comes from confidence.

---

# HERO SECTION

Height:

120vh

Split composition.

Left side:

Editorial content.

Micro label:

"Designed To Endure. Created To Inspire."

Main headline:

Timeless Design.
Unrivaled Experience.

Highlight the word:

Experience

using accent color.

Supporting text:

Obsidian Atelier creates collectible furniture and spaces for those who value artistry, heritage, and the future of design.

Primary CTA:

Explore Collections

Secondary CTA:

Book Concierge

Right side:

Large floating hero chair.

Rendered on a sculptural stone pedestal.

Behind the chair:

Massive metallic circular halo.

Subtle floating motion.

Soft spotlight.

Mouse-parallax movement.

A gold award seal floats partially between both columns.

Hero should immediately create a wow factor.

---

# TRUST BAR

Full width dark strip.

Four luxury principles:

Masterful Craftsmanship

Exceptional Materials

Timeless Design

Bespoke Service

Each with elegant iconography.

Subtle hover effects.

---

# SECTION 2

OUR PHILOSOPHY

Layout:

Editorial left column.

Three image cards right.

Headline:

Where Artistry Meets Purpose

Each card explains:

Crafted By Masters

Finest Materials

Design With Intent

Cards should animate into view.

Magazine-like spacing.

---

# SECTION 3

SIGNATURE EXPERIENCE

This is the most important section.

Must become the portfolio centerpiece.

Dark immersive section.

Large 3D furniture piece centered.

User can:

* rotate furniture
* change material
* change wood
* change fabric

Material swatches animate.

Furniture updates instantly.

Luxury configurator feel.

This section alone should feel better than many commercial websites.

---

# SECTION 4

CURATED COLLECTIONS

Editorial gallery.

Not a normal grid.

Layout:

Large feature card.

Two supporting cards.

Luxury photography.

Collections:

Luminara

Soffio

Solen

Hover:

Slow image zoom.

Luxury motion.

Elegant transitions.

---

# SECTION 5

MATERIAL LIBRARY

Headline:

The Beauty Is In The Details

Display:

Stone

Wood

Metal

Fabric

Large macro photography.

Hover reveals information.

Extremely tactile feeling.

Make visitors feel textures through visuals.

---

# SECTION 6

AWARDS & RECOGNITION

Dark luxury section.

Display:

Gold Award 2024

Best Of The Best 2024

A'Design Winner

IDA Mention

Metrics:

12+ Years Heritage

250+ Bespoke Projects

48 Countries Served

Use premium number animations.

---

# SECTION 7

IMMERSIVE SHOWROOM

Full-width cinematic section.

Parallax interior environment.

Slow scroll storytelling.

Text overlays.

Magazine feeling.

Almost feels like entering a luxury showroom.

---

# SECTION 8

CONCIERGE EXPERIENCE

Split layout.

Headline:

Let's Create Something Extraordinary Together

Description:

Whether you're designing a single room or an entire residence, our team brings your vision to life.

Primary CTA:

Book Private Consultation

Secondary CTA:

Chat With A Concierge

Elegant motion.

---

# FOOTER

Luxury editorial footer.

Dark background.

Large logo.

Navigation columns.

Social links.

Minimal.

Premium.

No clutter.

---

# ANIMATION SYSTEM

Use GSAP.

Use Lenis smooth scrolling.

Animations must feel:

* expensive
* smooth
* restrained

Never flashy.

Rules:

Elements reveal on scroll.

Images subtly scale.

Text slides elegantly.

Parallax only where beneficial.

Maximum sophistication.

---

# PERFORMANCE

Lighthouse:

95+

Must remain performant.

Lazy load images.

Optimize animations.

Avoid layout shifts.

---

# MOBILE EXPERIENCE

Not an afterthought.

Must feel equally luxurious.

Redesign layouts for mobile.

Maintain hierarchy.

Maintain storytelling.

Maintain visual impact.

---

# FINAL OBJECTIVE

When a visitor lands on the page they should think:

"This feels like a luxury brand worth millions."

When a designer lands on the page they should think:

"Who built this?"

When a potential client lands on the page they should think:

"I want this quality for my business."

Build every section to that standard.
